==English==

===Pronunciation===
*sīt, /<tt>saIt</tt>/
* {{IPA|/saɪt/}}
* [[Rhymes:English:-aɪt|Rhymes: -aɪt]]

====Homophones====
*[[cite]], [[sight]]

===Noun===
'''site'''  (''plural:'' [[sites]])

#The place where anything is fixed; situation; local position; as, the site of a city or of a house.
#A place fitted or chosen for any certain permanent use or occupation; as, a site for a church.
#The posture or position of a thing.

===Translations===
*Italian: [[posto]], [[circostanza]]
*Serbian: [[место]], [[градилиште (construction site)]]

===See also===
*[[website]]

===Verb===
'''to site''' (''third-person singular simple present'' [[sites]], ''present participle'' [[siting]], ''simple past'' [[sited]], ''past participle'' [[sited]])
[[Category:English verbs]]
#{{rfv-sense}}{{Architecture}} To [[situate]] or [[place]] a building.

